cicognara-catalogo.title: dcl:cp7, German, and Black Letter/ Gothic Script

comments.body:
Alright, image 72 is a sermon about witches and how God saves against them authored by M. Johann. Christoph. Müller a pastor in Witterstat . Couldn't find any info about the sermon, the pastor, or Witterstat and while is it said the pastor wrote this as a favor to his brother in law the overall author Schröter did not have a brother in law with that name.

Image 73 is a short telling of Walpurgis night and St. Walburga (here fashioned as a male) brought forward by the whole 'Tischgesellschaft' (table society - old term meaning a group of organizers since decisions are made at pub meetings). Walpurgis night is the night before first of May when witches meet on the Brocken mountain in Germany (it's a thing), so that fits in with the whole witches bad, God good theme.

below is the transcription of the beginning and end of the pages:


image 72 >> 'frag nicht ob hexen sein und eine solche Rotter 
die stets dem teufel steht durch schafen zu gebother /
[... devils, witches et cetera...]
habt ferner euren Gott im Herzen und vor Augen /
und lasst das rechte Recht in euren dienen taugen /
so [hafft?] zur Straff an euch sein harter Hexen-Knall /
Denn Gott ist euer [Trug?] / Schutz / Segen / Burg und Wall.

Dies anfertigte seinem Vielgeehrten Herrn Schw-
ager aus Bitte aus.

M. Johann. Christoph. Müller

Pastor in Witterstat [?]<<

image 73: >>Walpurgis nacht ist in aller Welt berühmt
[...]
Mit diesen Wenigen [wolec?] des Herrn Walburgers /
gelehrte Schrifft / wohlmeinend beehren
Die sämtliche Tischgesellschaft<<

comments.body: @kelea99 I did some digging around. Unfortunately, the images in `/Volumes/pudl/Vol4_pudl_merged_rm/gis` are just copies of images in another Isilon share. I think tracking down and ingesting the JPEG2000 derivatives is the only way to proceed in a timely manner. As far as I know, we don't have a way of ingesting JPEG2000 images directly as original files, but that is something we can work on.

@eliotjordan , alas and I'm so sorry it was a no-go with locating the tiffs.  Would it faster for us to convert the jp2s to tiffs pre-ingest for this time, while you all work on the future of jp2 ingest? @roelmoon and/or I could do it, I'm sure?

To test.

1. Reach out to James Robinson at BD to tell them we are testing. Ultimately when successful he will activate our production configuration to use encryption. 
2. Add new public key to the Orangelight group vars https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/1433. 
3. Encrypt the "PI" parameter with the public key provided by the Borrow Direct coordinator.
4. Change the RELAIS_BASE URL to the the BD test system configured for encryption with the accompanying private key.  https://sandbox.relais-host.com/user/login.html?group=patron 
5. Successfully test Borrow Direct route(s) in Orangelight with BD test system. 
6. Request Borrow Direct activate encryption in the production system.
